Review-Scraper

A Java + Selenium tool to scrape user reviews from platforms like G2 and Capterra (with optional third-source integration).
It lets you collect reviews for a product within a date range and outputs them in JSON format for easy analysis.

 Features

Scrape reviews from G2 and Capterra
Filter reviews by date range
Support for headless and non-headless modes
Output saved as structured JSON files
Extensible: easily integrate additional review sources

Setup & Installation
Requirements
Java 17+ (tested on JDK 23)
Maven 3.8+
Chrome/Chromium browser installed
Matching ChromeDriver (handled automatically if WebDriverManager is used)

Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/patnaikAnwesh/review-Scraper.git
cd review-Scraper

Build the JAR
mvn clean package


This generates the runnable JAR inside target/, e.g.:

target/review12-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar


(If you’ve configured the Shade plugin, you may see *-jar-with-dependencies.jar.)

 Usage

General command format:
java -jar target/review12-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar "<ProductName>" <StartDate> <EndDate> <Source> [options]

Example 1 – Scrape HubSpot reviews from Capterra
java -jar target/review12-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar "HubSpot" 2024-01-01 2024-12-31 capterra headless=false

Example 2 – Scrape Salesforce reviews from G2
java -jar target/review12-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar "Salesforce" 2024-01-01 2024-12-31 g2

Example 3 – Scrape from multiple sources
java -jar target/review12-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar "HubSpot" 2024-01-01 2024-12-31 g2,capterra headless=true

Arguments
Argument	Description
ProductName	Name of the product (e.g., "HubSpot")
StartDate	Start of the review range (yyyy-MM-dd)
EndDate	End of the review range (yyyy-MM-dd)
Source	Review source: g2, capterra, (or both as comma-separated)
headless	(Optional) true / false – run browser in headless mode
